          "username": "biny993"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-21 03:46:36.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nIt is great to have dedicate spec to design the image service. So would you please elaborate the consumers of this image service, and design the interaction and APIs between consumers and multicloud servcies(detail to framework and plugins which might be concerned)?\nAnd we are approaching code freeze quickly, so I wonder if this feature be still part of Beijing Release? \nThanks",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "0ab78a2e872991e670a378ec123b11520ab18efe",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1889,
          "name": "Bin Yang",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "bin.yang@windriver.com",
          "username": "biny993"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-21 14:42:01.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAs we discussed, please elaborate the design with following points:\n1, What the specific APIs format are\n2, Will the image service be synchronous API or asynchronous API? \n3, What the specific design in terms of interaction of multicloud framework and multicloud plugins.\nIt will be great to have some sequence diagram to clarify above points\nThanks.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
